<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB6FFE2FCCCF8D44B4CFD3E" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFE2FCCCF8D448C8FEBE" blockId="7.[801,1452,1793,1946]" lastBlockId="9.[113,764,279,719]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="102" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCCCF8D44AFEF8E8" box="[839,924,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFBFCF8D44C3BF8EB" author="BURMAN" box="[1143,1369,1793,1818]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="233" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 233)</bibRefCitation>
simply referred to an illustration (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFBB7F8F44D95F8CB" author="PETIVER" box="[1084,1271,1826,1850]" firstAuthor="PETIVER" journalOrPublisher="London" page="38" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref10058" refString="PETIVER, J. (1712). Pteri-graphia Americana. London." title="Pteri-graphia Americana" type="book" year="1712">PETIVER, 1712: 38</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 14, fig. 2) as (unnamed) variety 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFC6CF8944A94F8AB" box="[999,1014,1858,1882]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">β</emphasis>
. He did not mention any collector, merely “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCA0F8B44AAAF888" box="[811,968,1890,1914]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Habitat in 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFC11F8B44AAAF888" box="[922,968,1890,1913]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
” as locality. But his comment about the variety 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCAAF8544A52F86B" box="[801,816,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">β</emphasis>
(“[...] 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCF7F8544D04F868" box="[892,1126,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">cum javanica sit ovata</emphasis>
[...]”), a comparison between Petiver’s plate and an actual Javan specimen, may be regarded as implicit specimen citation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8597661CFFB9FFE3FF03F8424B87F856" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5708789" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5708789" box="[136,741,1940,1959]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5708789/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" startId="8.[136,164,1940,1959]" targetBox="[311,1299,276,1863]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB9FFE3FF03F8424B87F856" blockId="8.[136,741,1940,1959]" box="[136,741,1940,1959]" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB9FFE3FF03F84249A8F856" bold="true" box="[136,202,1940,1959]" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Fig. 4. –</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB9FFE3FEC2F8424B1FF856" authority="Burm. f." authorityName="Burm. f." box="[329,637,1940,1959]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adianthoides">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB9FFE3FEC2F8424B52F856" box="[329,560,1940,1959]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Polypodium adianthoides</emphasis>
Burm. f.
</taxonomicName>
in G-PREL.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FF1CFE814B9AFDFE" blockId="9.[113,764,279,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FF1CFE8149C9FE9E" box="[151,171,343,367]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">Asingle</collectionCode>
specimen of original material is extant in G-PREL [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FF6EFEA1499AFE7E" box="[229,248,375,399]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00348837]: it bears a reference to Petiver’s illustration and the name of the new species, both from 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FD1BFE414BC5FE5F" box="[656,679,407,430]" country="China" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13092" name="Nanjing University" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">N</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFB8FFE2FD20FE414BDDFE5F" box="[683,703,407,430]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. Burman’s hand, as well as a few notes by John Briquet (1870 – 1931), former curator of the Delessert Herbarium (“ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FDD8FE0E4985FDFE" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB8FFE2FDD8FE0E4BE0FE1E" box="[595,642,472,495]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Java</collectingRegion>
/ non filix / non Petiver
</emphasis>
” in front of the reference to Petiver’s illustration).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB8FFE2FF1CFDC14B4CFD3E" blockId="9.[113,764,279,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FF1CFDC148E6FDDE" author="MERRILL" box="[151,388,535,559]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="337" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 337)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB8FFE2FE6DFDC14BDFFDDE" box="[486,701,535,559]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovatum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FE6DFDC14BDFFDDE" box="[486,701,535,559]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Polypodium ovatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as of doubtful status. This name refers indeed to a commonly cultivated form of 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB8FFE2FE93FD814B46FD9E" box="[280,548,599,623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Plectranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scutellarioides">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FE93FD814B46FD9E" box="[280,548,599,623]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Plectranthus scutellarioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB8FFE2FDBFFD8E4BFDFD9E" box="[564,671,600,623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB8FFE2FDBFFD8E4BFDFD9E" box="[564,671,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">Lamiaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as correctly identified by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB8FFE2FECBFDA14B75FD7E" author="STEENIS" box="[320,535,631,655]" firstAuthor="STEENIS" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Jard. Bot. Buitenzorg" page="288" pageId="9" pageNumber="102" pagination="288" part="13" refId="ref10267" refString="STEENIS, C. G. G. J. VAN (1934). The identity of Polypodium ovatum Burm. f. Bull. Jard. Bot. Buitenzorg ser. 3, 13: 288." title="The identity of Polypodium ovatum Burm. f." type="journal article" year="1934">STEENIS (1934: 288)</bibRefCitation>
, who also designated the above specimen (seen as photograph!) as “actual 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB8FFE2FD05FD414BDFFD5E" box="[654,701,663,687]" pageId="9" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
”. This implicit lectotypification is accepted here.
</paragraph>
